Here are our favorite gift ideas for outdoor lovers!]]></description><content:encoded><![CDATA[<p class="sqsrte-large">Chocolate &amp; flowers are nice and all, but anything I can take camping immediately wins.</p><p class="">If you have entered a grocery store since the new year, you are more than aware that it is the season of LoOoVe! This valentines day, skip the chocolate and flowers (okay maybe a little chocolate…) and get your outdoorsy person something they will really love!</p><p class="">Here are our favorite gift ideas for outdoor lovers!</p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p><h3>Gifts for Him</h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Darn Tough Socks</p><p class="">I don’t care what holiday it is or how many pairs of these I already own, I will be STOKED to get <a href="https://amzn.to/3oj3Oya">Darn Tough Socks</a>! They are the best socks for hiking, keep my feet warm in the winter when I’m in the shop, and last forever. Like actually forever, the company will replace your socks if you somehow manage to destroy them. We both still have the same pairs we bought from REI for our first backpacking trip together 5 years ago.</p><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p>


















  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
              <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f997a4773370b1d7864046d/26d2dbd3-024f-4ec6-bc8d-0e9b47f6830a/IMG_7554.jpg" data-image-dimensions="4000x6000" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" data-image-id="61fab54183359819694ee0b4" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f997a4773370b1d7864046d/26d2dbd3-024f-4ec6-bc8d-0e9b47f6830a/IMG_7554.jpg?format=1000w" />
            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





<p class="sqsrte-large">Leatherman Multitool</p><p class="">We have <a href="https://amzn.to/349NbOE">The Wave Plus</a> and love it! This thing has come in handy so may times we have been camping. It’s compact, light, and easily fits in your backpack.</p><p class="">This multitool has a quiver of 18 tools, including pliers, knives, spring-action scissors, wire stripper, replaceable wire cutters, saw, ruler, files, screwdrivers, and<br>can &amp; bottle openers.<br><br></p><p class="sqsrte-large">Blades</p><p class="">Okay, so blades is a bit broad. But we’ll leave the specific type up to you! There are three blades we like to keep with us whenever we camp. </p><ol data-rte-list="default"><li><p class="">Hatchet. No man in the woods is a ‘real man’ without his trusty hatchet. Find one with a solid wood handle (Hickory, Oak or Ash) and high carbon steel head. It will outlast your children.</p></li><li><p class="">Folding Bushcraft Saw. We have the <a href="https://amzn.to/3ujdRHo">Bahco Laplander</a>. It folds up like a pocket knife and is perfect for sawing dead branches for firewood or building a bushcraft shelter.</p></li><li><p class=""><a href="https://www.bahco.com/us_en/multipurpose-tradesman-knives-with-dual-component-handle---15-pcs-counter-display-pb_2444_.html">Bahco 2444 Tradesman Knife</a>. This thing is super razor sharp stainless steel. This is different than a multi tool is, in that it does one thing well: CUT. It’s always good to have a sharp knife whether you need to shave wood or flint, or to cut a juicy steak.</p></li></ol><p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p>


















  

    
  
    

      

      
