        </figure>
      

    
  


  





<p data-rte-preserve-empty="true" class=""></p><p class="sqsrte-large">First Aid Kit</p><p class="">Nothing says I care about you like a kit to keep them safe. I (Danny) whipped out our<a href="https://amzn.to/349QBRu"> MyFAK</a> first aid kit from <a href="https://alnk.to/6xENf7f">My Medic</a> this past week after cutting myself in the shop. Whether we’re building a teardrop or traveling in one, we always are prepared when it comes to safety supplies, and hope you are too!</p><p class=""><br></p><p class="sqsrte-large">DIY Teardrop Plans</p><p class="">This one is for our handy men (and women) out there. If you are thinking about building a teardrop trailer, <a href="https://wandertears.com/diy-plans">our plans</a> are there to help you expedite the process, have confidence in your work, and provide you with all the materials, parts, cuts, and links you need to make it happen. </p><p class="">Here’s what current DIYer Charlie in Ireland had to say:</p><blockquote><p class="sqsrte-small">“Finding the going easy using the plans. They are a huge time save and easy to understand.  I am really enjoying the build.” </p></blockquote>


















  

    
  
    

      

      
