        </figure>
      

    
  


  





<h3>US</h3><p class="">We have been busy in the shop and behind the scenes working on custom teardrops and helping our DIY community with their builds. We (especially Paige) are very much over the cold weather (classic Florida girl) and ready to get back into nature for our next trip. We haven’t scheduled anything yet but will likely take the teardrop up to our favorite local spot by the lake this month and head to the Blue Ridge Mountains in March.</p>


















  

    
  
    

      

      
        <figure class="
              sqs-block-image-figure
              intrinsic
            "
        >
          
        
        

        
          
            
          
            
              <img class="thumb-image" data-image="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f997a4773370b1d7864046d/4646ddcb-7606-48b6-ad2c-ec1883e8c92f/IMG_2851.jpg" data-image-dimensions="2500x1875" data-image-focal-point="0.5,0.5" alt="" data-load="false" data-image-id="61f828166c672d52689c9d78" data-type="image" src="https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5f997a4773370b1d7864046d/4646ddcb-7606-48b6-ad2c-ec1883e8c92f/IMG_2851.jpg?format=1000w" />
            
          
        
          
        

        
      
        </figure>
      

    
  


  





<p class="">Our teardrop got a little update recently. We put on some bigger tires and black wheels, and we must say, it looks damn good! We had standard trailer tires, but switched to larger Wrangler Trailer Runner A/Ts. What do you think?</p><p class=""><br><br></p><h3>Builds </h3><p class="">We have several builds in progress and are steadily adding more to the queue. Production is going well and the supply chain hasn’t thrown too may curve balls at us recently, so we’re thankful for that! Next month we are getting a new piece of equipment that’s going to speed up production quite a bit. (We’ll share more soon!) We love our Vaga model, but are excited to have a few Renegade LT and Renegade AT orders in the queue. </p><p class="">Our All Terrain (AT) models are built on a heavy duty frame and have the option to add independent suspension and a lift. Our lightweight (LT) models can be towed by virtually any vehicle. You can check out our models and all the customizations <a href="https://wandertears.com/teardrop-models">here</a>.  </p>







  

  



  
    
      

        
          
            
              
