<h3>DIY </h3><p class="sqsrte-large">Plans</p><p class="">We are now helping teardrop builders across the globe! When you get our detailed <a href="https://wandertears.com/diy-plans">DIY plans</a> your are also invited to our private build community on Facebook. This is where DIYers share their progress and can ask any questions related to building their teardrop. </p><p class="">Something very cool that has also come from the group is individuals from different countries sharing information on where to get materials and parts that are more difficult to find outside of the US. (Our DIY plans include links and part numbers for all materials, however some companies doing ship internationally). </p><p class="">DIY Plans are available for the <a href="https://wandertears.com/diy-plans/p/renegade">Renegade</a>, <a href="https://wandertears.com/diy-plans/p/the-vaga-series-basic-plans">Vaga</a>, and <a href="https://wandertears.com/diy-plans/p/the-hopper-4x8-plans">Hopper</a> models. We also have added a <a href="https://wandertears.com/diy-plans/p/the-vaga-3d-model-with-layers">3D Vaga model with layers</a> to our DIY page so you can easily manipulate the free 3D Vaga model to better visualize the components. (This model is included in the DIY Plans).</p><p class="sqsrte-large">Trailer Frames</p><p class="">One of the most important parts of your teardrop build is the trailer frame. You want a strong foundation that can take you wherever you want to wander. Unfortunately, finding a quality trailer frame can also be one of the trickiest parts of the build process. </p><p class="">Upon popular request, we now supply <a href="https://wandertears.com/trailer-frames">steel trailer frames</a> for DIYers! </p><p class="">Not only will this guarantee a strong frame for you to start your build, but it comes with a VIN, Bill of Sale, and Certificate of Origin which will make your life much easier when it comes time to register your teardrop. </p>


















  

    
  
    

      

      
